.TH CMT_TYPES 3 "CMT" "CMT_TYPES" "Type Definitions and Support Macros"

.SH NAME
CMT_TYPES \- Standard and fixed-size types with support macros for portability

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__TYPES
.br
.B #include <CMT/CMT.H>

.SH FILES
CMT/KEYWORDS/TYPES.H

.SH DESCRIPTION
Provides standard types, fixed-size types, floating-point types, and macros to check 
support for platform-dependent types. Useful for portable code across compilers and architectures.

.SH STANDARD TYPES
.TP
.B BYTE, byte
Unsigned one byte storage unit (char)
.TP
.B LET, let
Type for array indexing and sizes (like \fIsize_t\fR)
.TP
.B VAR, var
Type capable of holding maximum addressable value
.TP
.B PTR, ptr
Generic pointer type

.SH TYPES WITH FIXED SIZES
.TP
.B BIT8, bit8
8-bit unsigned or signed integer
.TP
.B BIT16, bit16
16-bit unsigned or signed integer
.TP
.B BIT32, bit32
32-bit unsigned or signed integer
.TP
.B BIT64, bit64
64-bit unsigned or signed integer
.TP
.B BIT128, bit128
128-bit unsigned or signed integer (if supported)

.SH FLOATING-POINT TYPES
.TP
.B FLOAT32, float32
32-bit single-precision floating-point
.TP
.B FLOAT64, float64
64-bit double-precision floating-point
.TP
.B FLOAT128, float128
128-bit extended-precision floating-point (if supported)

.SH MACROS TO CHECK SUPPORT OF TYPES
.TP
.B SUPPORTED__BIT64
Defined if compiler supports BIT64 type
.TP
.B SUPPORTED__BIT128
Defined if compiler supports BIT128 type
.TP
.B SUPPORTED__FLOAT64
Defined if compiler supports FLOAT64 type
.TP
.B SUPPORTED__FLOAT128
Defined if compiler supports FLOAT128 type

.SH NOTES
- Some types may not be defined if the platform or compiler does not support them.  
- For example, FLOAT64 may not be available if the native \fIdouble\fR type is only 32 bits.  
- Similarly, FLOAT128 and BIT128 are only defined if the compiler and architecture support 128-bit values.  
- Users should check the corresponding macros (e.g., SUPPORTED__FLOAT64, SUPPORTED__FLOAT128, SUPPORTED__BIT128) before using these types to ensure portability and correctness.

